    'A large brown floral decorated <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03q7p08">stoneware</a> charger (1990) by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> ceramicist, Joan Vercuiel. The surface of the charger is decorated with a daisy-like floral pattern as <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0975t">clay</a> is finely folded, making the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c9ph5">flowers</a> appear embedded and tucked into the surface. It was donated by ceramics SA''s Northern Transvaal Branch in 1990',
