    'World War I Dutch Sociï¿½tï¿½ <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01x5q">Cï¿½ramique</a> Out of Danger plate, designed by Joseph Frenay. The female figure wearing a crown inscribed with the letter ï¿½Nï¿½ (Netherlands) is the Virgin of Holland and the figure in the blue dress is the symbolic mother of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0154j">Belgium</a>. The plate is inscribed, "Buiten Gevaar" meaning ï¿½Out of Dangerï¿½ commemorating the million war refugees that The Netherlands took in during the First <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0cm2xh">World War (1914-1918</a>).',
