    'Ruth Prowse',
    '1936',
    'From a <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0d4v4">Window</a>, Wale Street, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01yj2">Cape Town</a> was painted by the South African Artist Ruth Prowse (1883-1967). The painting was painted from the building on the corner of Wale and Adderley Street with the fence in the background being the Garden of the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> Museum in Cape Town. The painting was donated to the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> by the artist for use by the Art History Department in the 1940s.',
