    'Oz Achterburgwal is an etching done by <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">the Dutch</a> artist Cornelius Brandenburg (1883-1954) in 1920. The Oz in the title is an abbreviation for the word <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/g12pgcxdq9">Oudezijds</a> or Old-fashioned. The location depicted is in the center of De Wallen in Amsterdam, today this is the cities red light district. Short Biography: Cornelis (Cor) Brandenburg was born in Wormerveer in 1883. He studied at the Drawing School for <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01mrgs">Craft</a> in 1890 and at the Academy for Fine Arts in Amsterdam. He started out as a ceramic painter at ï¿½de Distelï¿½ factory from about 1903 but by the 1920s he was well established as a graphic artist. Brandenburg passes away in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0k3p">Amsterdam in</a> 1954.',
