    'Salmon Verveer',
    '1855',
    'An oil on Canvas dated 1855 by the Dutch artist, Salmon Leonardus Verveer (1813-1876) titled,  Evening mood or Avondstemming. The painting depicts a river landscape with a church and human figures. The top two thirds of the painting comprise an evening sky with clouds. Just left of the center is the church of the town <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03zslz">Spaarndam</a>. The painting was first exhibited with the title of Spaarndam in 1871 at the Exhibition of Living Artists in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0k3p">Amsterdam</a> (number 500 in the catalogue). The work appears in records of the artist dealer named, Pieter A. Scheen in 1951 when Alexander Johannes (Lex) Dingjan (1927-1985) photographed it for the Gallery. It is catalogued by the art dealer or Kunsthandel Pieter A Scheen titled, Avondstemming. Scheen sold the work at the Auction house, Van Marle, de Sille &amp; Baan in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06hdk">Rotterdam</a> on 28-30 May 1952, Lot 55.J A van Tilburg (1888-1980) purchased this work presumably on auction and it remained in this collection until 1957 when it was imported into <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South Africa</a> and he then bequeathed his vast collection in 1976 to the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>.',
