    'Circuit I is a woodblock print by the South African artist Gerhard Marx (b.1976). Short Biography: Gerhard Marx, a prominent South African artist, was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a> in 1976 and obtained his Bachelor''s degree in Fine Arts from the University of the Witwatersrand in 1998. He continued his academic pursuit and completed his Master''s degree in Fine Arts at the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01yj2">Cape Town</a>, where he graduated with the highest honors in 2004. Marx''s artistic expression is diverse and encompasses various mediums, including <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a>, printmaking, drawing, and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m012z_m">installation art</a>. His works often delve into complex issues of identity, memory, and place, with a particular emphasis on <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South Africa''s</a> intricate social and political history.',
