    'Andre Otto',
    '1990',
    'A <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01brf">bronze</a> sculpture titled Musaion by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Andre Otto. The <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a> depicts an ancient harp fused with a crossbow and is located at the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>''s Music Department, a building which is also named the Musaion. Short biography: Otto obtained a BA (Fine Arts) degree at the University of Pretoria. He produces art full-time and also works in the commercial field of architectural sculpture and design; he worked in association with AWW/Themeworks and Olio (<a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09c7w0">USA</a>) on the Atlantis project, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03m6c6">Palm Island</a>, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01f08r">Dubai</a>, creating bronze and fibre works. Otto has participated in in a number of group exhibitions and competitions since 1984, including the New Signatures, ABSA L''Atelier and Ekurhuleni  competitions, and held his first solo show in 2002. Otto has executed a number of private and corporate commissions, including Musaion Sculpture.',
