    'A <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m018ktp">Watercolor painting</a> by the Italian artist Giulio Falzoni (1900-1979) titled, Church Lucca done in 1945. It is unsure which church in the town of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0cht6">Lucca</a> this is. Short Biography: Giulio Falzoni was born in Mantua in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03rjj">Italy</a> in 1900. He studied at the Academy of Fine Arts in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m031y2">Florence</a> and was a student of the Watercolorist, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0h7l221">Plinio Nomellini</a> (1866-1943). In 1940, after visiting <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m04jpl">London</a> he became attracted to the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07ssc">British</a> Watercolor style and also became a member of the London Society of Watercolorist. Falzoni is known as the last of the great Italian Watercolorists. This work was donated to the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> by JA van Tilburg in 1980, who purchased the work from an exhibition held in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South Africa</a> of the works of Giulio Falzoni, as well as his son Giordano (1925-1998). The Van Tilburg donation to the University of Pretoria in 1980, included 125 Watercolors by Giulio Falzoni.',
