    'Michael Mmutle',
    '2003',
    'A painting titled Marabastad by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Mike Mmutle (1948-2010). Marabastad is part of the central Business district of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>, it was named after the Ndebele Chief Maraba. Mmutle''s parents lived in 1st Avenue in Marabastad but was moved by the Apartheids Government to Bantuli Village in 1952. He kept close ties to this part of the city and most of his works was painted here. Short Biography: Born in Marabastad in 1948, Mmutle had a very unstable childhood due to Apartheid, his Family moved from Marabastad in 1952 to Bantuli, to Lady Selborne in 1956, Atteridgeville in 1957 and Ga-Rankuwa in 1967. He was taught by the fellow artist <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c4l7x">Walter Battiss</a> and became part of the Ga-Rankuwa group in the 1970s. In 2001 he became the Departmental Head of Fine Arts Department at Arts For All. he passed away in Pretoria in 2010.',
