    'Mike Edwards',
    '1980',
    'A work titled Vertical by the South African artist Mike Edwards. Vertical has a simple and elegant design. The work is an abstract column which is well balanced with an upward movement. Vertical is typical of modernist geometrical works of the 1980s. Vertical was created for a large <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a> exhibition curated by the artist which was held on the University of Pretoria''s Hatfield campus during 1980. After the exhibition the work was placed in front of the Visual Arts Building by Edwards himself. Edwards was during that time a lecturer in Fine Arts at the University of Pretoria. Short biography: Mike Edwards was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06f0y3">Port Elizabeth</a> South Africa in 1938. In 1991, he settled in the Cradle of Humankind area, in the north of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a>. He studied art at the Port Elizabeth Art School where he gained the National Art Teachers Certificate. Edwards subsequently obtained a BA and MA in Fine Arts from the University of Pretoria. His first teaching position was in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c499">Bloemfontein</a> where he became Head of the Art Department and Vice-Principal of the then Technical College. In 1973, Edwards accepted a post as a lecturer at the University of Pretoria, later becoming Associate Professor of Fine Art. In 1990, he left teaching to become a full-time practicing artist. He has undertaken numerous visits overseas where he particularly studied bronze as a medium in sculpture. These included foundries in America, the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07ssc">United Kingdom</a>, France and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03rjj">Italy</a> and the facility of Hermann Noack in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0156q">Berlin</a>. Edward received many commissions, including a twenty meter high <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06qqv">stainless steel</a> sculpture in Pretoria, the Delville Wood Panel in Longueval, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0f8l9c">France</a>, and many portraits of public figures, academics and fellow artists. He has works in public buildings in South Africa such as the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> Medical and Dental Council, State Theatre, Civitas and Momentum Life, all in Pretoria, and some provincial buildings of the Free State. Edwards has exhibited in group shows since 1959, in South Africa, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09c7w0">America</a>, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0345h">Germany</a>, and the UK. Edwards has a renowned artist''s career in portraiture with over 154 portraits completed spanning fifty years, 1958-2008. His iconic works are found in several notable collections in the University of Pretoria, University of the Free State, the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> Art Museum, as well as in many private collections in South Africa and internationally.',
