    'A bronze portrait dated 1964 by the South African artist Nell Kaye (1912-1969) of the renowned <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hrf0cv">Maggie Laubser</a> (1886-1973). Sort Biography: Nell Kaye was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a> in 1912 and exclusively created <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01brf">bronze</a> busts. She studied at the Witwatersrand Technical College Art School in the 1930s and at the Michaelis School of Art in the 1950s in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01yj2">Cape Town</a>. Kaye passed away in Rondebosch in the Western Cape in 1969.',
