    'Nyala is a painting by <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m05bmq">Namibian</a> / <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> wildlife artist Zakkie Eloff (1925-2003). Eloff lived in Witrivier near the Kruger <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m05gz5">National Park</a> and spent a large portion of his life painting and drawing the wildlife of South Africa here. The Nyala is a spiral horned antelope native to Southern <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0dg3n1">Africa</a>. Short Biography: Zacharias (Zakkie) Eloff was born in 1925 in the Waterberg district of Namibia. He studied under <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c4l7x">Walter Battiss</a> and Maurice van Essche as well as at the University of Pretoria. The University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> held a retrospective exhibition for Eloff in 1987 where this work was purchased.',
