    'A sculpture titled, On Land and Water by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> sculptor Angus Taylor (b.1970). The work is part of a series that was exhibited in 1999 at the Open Window Contemporary Gallery, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> and later in 2001 Gallery 88 in the town of Sasolburg, South Africa in a solo exhibition titled, "<a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0dg3n1">Africana</a> and other Baggage". Short biography: Angus Van Zyl Taylor was born in 1970 and is a well-known artist in South Africa and internationally for his powerful, monumental and large scale <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculptures</a>, often working in a medium that intimidates other artists. Taylor is a graduate of the University of Pretoria which bestowed an Alumni Laureate on him in 2005. In 1994 he won the first prize in the PPC Young Concrete Sculptor Award. In 1997, he founded Dionysus Sculpture Works, where he casts his own and other sculptors'' work and he encourages the talent of young developing artists. In addition to numerous solo and group exhibitions, Taylor is predominantly involved in large scale commissions for national and local government and the private sector.',
