    'Shenaz Mahomed',
    '2020',
    'An <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m012z_m">installation sculpture</a> titled, Be Civil by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Shenaz Mahomed (b.1992)The work was commissioned  by the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> in 2020 for the Engineering 4.0 Building which houses the Transport Department of Civil Engineering at the University of Pretoria. Mahomed''s work bridges the gap between civil engineering, aspects of transport and creative arts of humanities with the title "Be Civil". She accomplishes this using different mediums such as tyre tracks, as well as different languages to express the title. Short Biography: Shenaz Mahomed was born in Pretoria in 1992. Mahomed obtained both her undergraduate in 2014 and a  Masters degree in Fine Arts in 2018 from the University of Pretoria. She worked as a Curator at Fried Contemporary Art Gallery until its closure. She was alsoy Curatorial Assistant and Logistics Manager at Javett Art Centre at the University of Pretoria. In 2016, Mahomed won the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0gx02sn">David Koloane</a> Award which entitled her to a residency at the Bag Factory Art Studios as well as an opportunity to present her work at the FNB Joburg Art Fair. She has collaborated with other artists and participated in numerous group exhibitions. Mohamed currently is a lecturer in the Department of Fine Arts at the University of Pretoria.',
