    'A linocut by <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Thabang Lehobye (b.1986) titled Mpumalanga Journey II. The work is part of series which the artist made whilst traveling through Mpumalanga looking at the landscape and the deterioration there off. Short Biography: Thabang Lehobye was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0729t">Soweto</a> in 1986 and grew up in Evaton. He completed a certificate in printmaking at the Artist Proof Studio in 2003, a Degree in Fine Art at the University of Johannesburg and an Honours Degree at the Vega School in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a>. Today he work at FCB <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0dg3n1">Africa</a>, a branding company and still created exhibits his artworks.',
