    '1913',
    'Rooi Windpomp (Red Windpump) was created by <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Abraham Makhabela. Makhabela was born in Marble Hall district and came to work at the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> in 1987 as an assistant technician in the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a> studios. His work greatly sought after by many collectors and he participated in national art competitions such as the Sasol New Signatures Awards and the PPC Young Concrete Sculptors Competition. Makhabela passed away in 2007. Makhabela''s work had a deep religious conviction which always permeated his work. Conventional compositions and techniques are borrowed from the history of art and rendered with personal view.',
