    'Jean Henri Schuilenburg',
    '1945',
    'A Dutch Delft <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m04825h">De Porceleyne Fles</a> Victory tile designed by Jean Henri Schuilenburg (1882-1964). The tile depicts a sun with a <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m096mb">Lion</a> rampant on it rising from a flooded landscape. The tile is inscribed with the words, " The Netherlands will rise again 5 May 1945". On 5 May 1945 the Netherlands was officially liberated exactly five years to the day of the first German occupation in 1940. This tile shows the Lion, which is the Dutch National symbol and thus rising from the land ruined by war. Short Biography: Not much is known of Jean Henri Schuilenburg. He was born on 24 November 1882 in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m029t1">Delft</a> in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">The Netherlands</a> and is shown as an artist on his <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m04ztj">marriage</a> certificate in 1910. He passed away in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0wbxv">Rijswijk</a> in The Netherlands on 3 March 1964.',
