    'A lithograph print of a painting by Jan van Call of "Het Huis ten Bosch" or The House in the Woods, where the original painting was painted in 1690. The location of the original by Jan van Call (1655-1703) is not known, but this lithographic print was done for a book in the 1920s. Several artists used this painting to create other works showing a house in a wooded area just outside <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07g0_">The Hague</a> in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">The Netherlands</a>. The house was apparently built between 1645 and 1652 for Amelia van Solms, the Princess of Orange.',
