    'Sydney Moema',
    '1977',
    'A painting of a Mother and Child by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06y57">Sydney</a> Moema. The work shows a mother holding her child by the back of the head guiding him through the streets of the township. Short Biography: Sydney Patrick Moema was born in 1954 in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>. He studied at Rorke''s Drift Art Centre from 1974 to 1976 and at the Universitï¿½ per Stranieri di <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0dly0">Perugia</a> in 1984 and 1985. In the mid 1980s he works as a book illustrator and a television art teacher after which he practise as an artist.',
