    'Rina Stutzer',
    '2002',
    'A painting  titled, Sunday  by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist, Rina Stutzer (b.1976). The work depicts a woman selling flowers on a Sunday, a reality for most South African informal traders. On her back in a sling, she carries flowers instead of a baby. The <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c9ph5">flowers</a> on her back serves as a metaphor for her having to work for a living on a Sunday, instead of spending time with her child. Short Biography: Rina Stutzer was born in Vryheid in South Africa in 1976. She studied art at the University of Pretoria completing her Bachelor''s degree in 1999 and her Masters in 2007.  Stutzer works for the Dionysus Sculpture Works in Silverton, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>.',
