    'Portrait of Prof CWI Pistorius by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Cyril Coetzee (b.1958). Prof Carl Wilhelm Irene Pistorius (b. 1958) was the eleventh Principal of the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> and his tenure stretched between 2001 and 2009. The official collecting of portraits and the foundation of the Collection began on 9 September 1974. Prof A.N. Pelzer suggested that the University commence a collection of portraits of former Chancellors, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01mzpv">Chairs</a> of the Council and Principals. Between 1974 and 2010 the line-up of previous Principals and Chancellors were completed, a tradition that is still continuing with new appointments within the University of Pretoria.Short Biography: Cyril Coetzee was born in 1959 in Grahamstown in the Eastern Cape. He studied at Rhodes University and obtained his Masters qualification in 1983.',
