    'Vuminkosi Zulu',
    '1977',
    'A work titled, Ukubekwa Kwenkosi Ushaka, translated from Xhosa into English as The Enthronement of the King by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Vuminkosi Zulu (1948-1996). Short Biography: Vuminkosi Zulu was a South African artist born in 1948 and died in 1996. He completed his education at Kranskop High School and then enrolled at the Rorke''s Drift Art and Craft Centre. He was awarded the Hajee Sulman Ebrahim Memorial Trust award in 1973 and is known for his etchings and carved sculptures. His work was showcased in exhibitions both in South Africa and overseas, and he was widely recognized for his artistic talent and cultural significance. Before his death, he worked at the Caversham Press in the KwaZulu-Natal midlands and was a recipient of the Thupelo scholarship in 1990.',
