    'A woodcut by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Sokhaya Charles Nkosi titled Cows in the Camp. The image of five bulls in one camp is quite powerful as this would spell certain doom. The bulls shown here are most certainly Nguni, a Zulu cattle breed and a most prized possession. No good farmer would put his bulls into one camp like this. Short Biography: Sokhaya Charles Basil Nkosi was born in 1949 in Durban, KwaZulu Natal. He studied at Rorke''s Drift Art Centre from 1974 to 1976 on a bursary. After that he became a lecturer at several institutions such as the Open School in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01tjvv">Durban</a> AIA and FUNDA.',
