    'Three Boys Fishing was done by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist and cartoonist Andre de Beer (b.1933) in 1991. De Beer was well known for his character studies and loved to paint his children. Although they were quite a bit older at this stage the painting shows his sons at a young age. Short Biography: Andre de Beer was born in Potchefstroom in 1933. He obtained his BA degree in Fine Art from the University of Pretoria in 1953 and his MA degree in 1970, From 1958 he was an art lecturer at the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> Educational College, in 1970 he became head of the department of art and in 1979 he became Vice-Principal. In 1983 he retired to become a full time artist. De Beer is probably best known for his cartoons and character studies and was a political cartoonist for the Hoofstad NewsPaper from 1975-1977.',
