    'Walter Meyer',
    '1994',
    'A large canvas painting by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Walter Meyer (1965-2017) painted in 1994. Meyer painted Karoo scenes and had a great affinity for landscapes. Like this painting of a road between Upington and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01yj2">Cape Town</a>, many of his works were desolate and showed the disintegration of society through infrastructure. Short Biography: Carl Walter Meyer was born in Aliwal North in the Eastern Cape in 1965. He studied at the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> under Nico Roos in 1983-1984 and in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hf7l">Dusseldorf</a>, West <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0345h">Germany</a>. He became known for his large landscapes. Meyer was found murdered in his home in Upington in December 2017.',
