    'A painting by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> Artist Jean Luntz (b.1919) titled District Six. In the heart of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01yj2">Cape Town</a> was a community in the suburb called district six, between 1968 and 1982 more than 60 000 people were forcibly removed from this area by the Apartheids Government. Many artists during that time painted the area due to the lives and rich heritage that were destroyed by the government. Short Biography: Jean Luntz was born in 1919, she was an artist, poet, writer and political activist. In the 1950s she was an active writer for The Black Sash. She started painting in 1955 and first exhibited in 1964.',
