    'A lithograph titled, Parking (2001) produced by the South Africa artist, Jabulani <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/g113r34hl5">Sam Nhlengethwa</a> (b.1955) from his Josi Series (Josi is an acronym for <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a>). The series of lithographs were printed in an edition of 30 and is about everyday life in the City of Johannesburg, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South Africa</a>. Nhlengethwa was born in 1955 in Springs in the township of Payneville. In 1977 and 1978, he completed his studies at the Rorkeï¿½s Drift Art School. Nhlengethwaï¿½s most prominent works are about the subject of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03_d0">Jazz</a>. His family were Jazz enthusiasts and his elder brother was a Jazz Musician.',
