    'Theo Goedfriend',
    '1936',
    'An <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03yhk">ink</a> painting titled Wetland by the Dutch <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Theo Goedvriend (1879-1969). The work was donated by the artist after his 1937 exhibition at the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>. Short Biography: Theodoor Franciscus (Theo) Goedvriend was born in 1879 in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0zrs187">De Steeg</a>, Rheden, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">The Netherlands</a>. He studies under AJ Derkinderen in 1897 and at the Kunstnijverheidsschool in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0k3p">Amsterdam in</a> 1899. Moved to South Africa in 1936 and had his first exhibition in the country 1937. He gave Art History at the University of Pretoria in 1938. He went to <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03ryn">Indonesia</a> in 1941 to help with the war effort and was imprisoned in an Japanese prisoner of war camp until 1944 when he moved back to the Netherlands. He passed away in 1969 in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m02p0ykh">Warnsveld</a>, The Netherlands.',
