    'Frikkie Kruger',
    '1928',
    'This work, titled The Hammer Worker was created by the South African sculptor Frederick Johannes (Frikkie) Kruger (1907-1966). For decades this particular work was thought to be that of the sculptor, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09n5cb">Anton van Wouw</a>. The Hammer Worker was a <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a> left by Kruger at Van Wouw''s House when Kruger was a student of Van Wouw. It was gifted by Van Wouw to a visitor in 1928. In 1931, the work was exhibited at the 12th <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> Academy Exhibition in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a> by Frikkie Kruger and it was described by the media as an "amateurish copy of Van Wouwï¿½s work"',
