    'A Napoleonic War Dutch Plateelbakkerij Delft or Pottery Bakery Delft commemorative plate is one of a set consisting of 14 plates. The pottery that made these, although they had <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m029t1">Delft</a>, a town in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">The Netherlands</a> in their name was made in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0k3p">Amsterdam</a>. Decorated in blue and red the plate commemorates the Battle of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0jpkg">Waterloo</a> on 18 June 1815 as well as the important role players in the battle namely Prince Willem of Orange of the Netherlands, Field marshal Gebhard Leberecht von Blï¿½cher and Arthur Wellesley the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m02c4s">1st Duke of Wellington</a>. The plate was donated by Louise van Gybland Oosterhoff to the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> in 1937.',
