    'Mike Edwards',
    '2008',
    'A cemcrete portrait of Dr Andrï¿½ Breedt by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> sculptor Mike Edwards (b.1938) completed in 2008. Breedt was the Head of Cultural Affairs (formerly the Cultural Bureau) and was a key figure in the post-1994 establishment of the Museum Unit at the University of Pretoria Campus. In 2008, Breedt managed the centenary celebrations of the University of Pretoria (1908-2008) and was the founder of the first group that established a dedicated art centre on the Hatfield campus, today the Javett-UP Arts Centre. Short Biography: Mike Edwards was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06f0y3">Port Elizabeth</a>, South Africa in 1938. In 1991, he settled in the Cradle of Humankind area, north of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a>. He studied art at the Port Elizabeth Art School where he gained the National Art Teachers Certificate. He subsequently obtained a BA and MA in Fine Arts from the University of Pretoria. His first teaching post was in Bloemfontein where he became Head of the Art Department and Vice-Principal of the then Technical College. In 1973, he accepted a post as a lecturer at the University of Pretoria, later becoming Associate Professor of Fine Art. In 1990, he left teaching to become a full-time practicing artist. He has undertaken numerous visits overseas where has made a particular study of bronze as a medium for sculpture. These included foundries in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09c7w0">the United States</a>, the United Kingdom, France and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03rjj">Italy</a>, as well as the facility of Hermann Noack in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0156q">Berlin</a>. Edward received many commissions, including a 20m high, stainless steel <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a> in Pretoria, the Delville Wood Panel in Longueval, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0f8l9c">France</a>, as well as many portraits of public figures, academics and fellow artists. Some of his works are in public buildings in South Africa, such as the South African Medical and Dental Council, State Theatre, Civitas, and Momentum Life, all located in Pretoria. Some of his works can also be found in provincial buildings of the Free State province, South Africa. Edwards has exhibited in group shows since 1959 in South Africa, the United States, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0345h">Germany</a>, and the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07ssc">United Kingdom</a>. Edwards has a renowned artist''s career in portraiture with over 154 portraits completed spanning fifty years, 1958-2008. His iconic works are found in several notable collections in the University of Pretoria, University of Johannesburg, University of Potchefstroom, University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c499">Bloemfontein</a>, in the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> Art Museum, as well as in many private collections in South Africa and internationally.',
