(
    'Marinus Pieter Reus',
    '1918',
    'A small 1918 <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c3yk">charcoal drawing</a> of a <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03k3r">horse</a>-drawn hearse by the Dutch artist Marinus Pieter (MP) Reus (1865-1938). Mr JA van Tilburg bequeathed his "prentenkabinet" or painting cabinet of over 10 000 graphic works to the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> in 1976. Over 2600 of these works are small sketches and watercolours by the Dutch Impressionist, M P Reus, the largest known collection of its kind. Van Tilburg bought all these works from the estate sale of Reus in 1939. Short Biography: Marinus Petrus Reus or MP Reus as he was known by the artworld was born in 1865 in Dordrecht in The Netherlands. He was mostly a self-taught artist and worked in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0jcx1">Dordrecht</a> for most of his life. He painted and drew in the Dutch Impressionist style. Reus passed away in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0vl48">Bergen op Zoom</a> in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">The Netherlands</a> in 1938.',
