    'Thulani Mntungwa & Jabu Nene',
    '2022',
    'Pangolin and Crocodile Circular Sculpture created at the Ardmore studio in KwaZulu Natal. Thulani Mntungwa has crafted an extraordinary piece of art that features a coiled <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a> of both a pangolin and a crocodile, creating a harmonious union between the two animals. The artwork has been masterfully painted by Jabu Nene, a celebrated artist known for her intricate geometric designs, with a rich palette of brown and yellow earth tones adding intricate detail to the piece. Short Biography: Thulani was born on the 4th of April, 1987 at kwaHaza. He attended school in Balgowan and finished in 2006 after which he started to work at the Ardmore studio as a sculptor.  Jabu Nene was first introduced to the world of art at the age of 15. She then went on to join the highly regarded Ardmore art team in 1991, where she was mentored by the famous Punch Shabalala. Jabu''s artistic style is truly one-of-a-kind, with intricate designs that stem from her vivid imagination. Her pieces feature geometric patterns and earthy tones, including zigzags, chevrons, squares, and soft pinks paired with rich browns. To add a unique touch, she uses a sharp wire to scratch into her paint, creating a sgraffito effect that sets her work apart.',
