    'Paul Ramagaga',
    '1952',
    'A <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m018ktp">Watercolor painting</a> by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Senthso Paul Ramagaga (1919-1995) titled Homecoming done in 1952. The painting is of a hut with two female figures sitting busy with house chores. On the left a man, probably a migration worker is seen greeting the woman as he returns from his labors. Short Biography: Senthso Paul Ramagaga was born in 1920 in Parys in the Free State where he lived with his Grandmother on a Farm called Regina. He completed standard six at the Moroka Missionary Institute in Thabaï¿½Nchu and moved to <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a> in 1935 where he started to work for an art framing company. He studied art part-time under the tutelage of Rene Shapshak in Yeoville from 1948 to 1953. Ramagaga tutored several other artists in the following years which include James Salang, Durant Sihlali and Ephraim Ngatane, all who became famous artists of the 1960s. Ramagaga passed away from a stroke on 12 September 1995.',
