    'P van der Want',
    '1919',
    '<a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0cm2xh">World War I</a> Dutch Ivora peace plate created by the P van der Want Plateelbakkerij Ivora or Ivora <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01x5q">Ceramic</a> Kiln, in the town of Gouda in 1919. This example is one of a series of 15 plates made by Ivora, Gouda commemorating peace after the war. It is decorated with orange symbolism and emblazoned with a central call, ï¿½Oranje Boven!ï¿½ and the inscription ï¿½Zoo wie de oude vrijheit mind dat is een regte oranje vrindï¿½ translated as ï¿½He who loves freedom is a friend of The Netherlandsï¿½.',
