    'Cyril Coetzee',
    '2010',
    'Portrait of Prof FP Smit by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist, Cyril Coetzee (b.1936). Prof Phillipus Smit (b. 1936) was the ninth Principal of the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> and his tenure stretched between 1992 and 1996. The official collecting of portraits and the foundation of the Collection began on 9 September 1974. Prof A.N. Pelzer suggested that the University commence a collection of portraits of previous Chancellors, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01mzpv">Chairs</a> of the Council and Principals. Between 1974 and 2010, the line-up of former Principals and Chancellors were completed, a tradition that is still continuing with new appointments. Short Biography: Cyril Coetzee was born in 1959 in Grahamstown in the Eastern Cape. He studied at Rhodes University and obtained his Masters qualification in 1983.',
