    'A portrait of Carl Buchner by South African artist Hannatjie van der Wat-Schabort (1923-2020). This is a portrait of the painter Carl Buchner (1921-2003) as a student. Between 1941 and 1944 Buchner and Schabort studied together at the Wits Technical College Art School where she created this work as one of her student exercises. Short Biography: Hannatjie van der Wat was born in Frankfort in the Free State in 1923. In 1941 she came to <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a> to study at the Witwatersrand Technical College Art School under Maurice van Essche. After getting <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m04ztj">married</a> she started to paint under Hannatjie van der Wat. In 2018 she was awarded the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> Academy for Science and Art <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m020yd1">Medal</a> of Honor for her work in uplifting female artist in South Africa as well as being a trailblazer in abstract expressionism. Van der Wat passed away in 2020.',
