    'This Dutch commemorative cup depicts a transfer print of the Prince of Orange leading the Dutch army in the Battle of Ravels on 3 August 1831. The transfer decoration was taken from a painting done by <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0j9qgfr">Johannes Jelgerhuis</a> (1770-1838) in 1831. The <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0gbkr6">Ten Days Campaign</a> or <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0154j">Belgian</a> Revolt occurred from 2-12 August 1831 and resulted in initial <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">Dutch</a> military success against the Belgians, but they withdrew as the French engaged in the war. The cup was donated by Louise van Gybland Oosterhoff to the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> in 1937.',
