    'Themba Khumalo',
    '2013',
    'An etching titled, The Generator by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist, Themba Khumalo (b.1987).  Short Biography: Themba Benedict Khumalo was born 16 February 1987 in Orange Farm, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0729t">Soweto</a> near <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a>. He graduated from the Artist Proof Studio, specialising in printmaking and obtained a Design Foundation Certificate. He went on to do a professional printmaking development course under the sponsorship of Pinpoint One, at Artist Proof Studio in 2009 where he was an intern in the silkscreen unit and special project team. Khumalo''s artistic pursuits extend beyond printmaking, as he also explores various other mediums such as charcoal drawings and painting. Central to Khumalo''s work is his reflection of the social, political, and spiritual landscape of contemporary South Africa, particularly emphasizing the concept of land as identity. Drawing inspiration from current news headlines, he delves into the injustices witnessed by the land. He has been involved in a number of group exhibitions, commissions and special projects, such as painting murals in the Eastern Cape and being invited to exhibit in a group show at Isolate del Cinema festival in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06c62">Rome</a>, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03rjj">Italy</a>. Khumalo resides and works in Johannesburg, operating from his studio located at August House. As an artists'' hub, August House was established as an enclave for African artists in 2006 by Bie Venter and Maria Svane and today hosts up to 40 contemporary private studios.',
