    'INRI- Crucifixion by the Italian-born <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Armando Baldinelli (1908-2002). The work was created in 1964 as part of a pre-study of a series on the Crucifixion which the artist produced as a mosaic installation for Pollie''s Arcade in the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> City Centre. Short Biography: Armando Baldinelli was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0dtyg">Ancona</a> <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03rjj">Italy</a> in 1908. He studied at the Academy of Fine Arts in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06c62">Rome</a> from 1925-1928. In 1950, his wife Gianna died in a car accident at age 26 and Baldinelli withdrew from society. A friend that was managing the Carlton Hotel in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a> suggested that Baldinello visit South Africa in 1953. He built his studio in Oaklands Johannesburg where he lived until he passed away in 2002.',
