    'Sydney Carter',
    '1930',
    'A <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m018ktp">watercolour painting</a> titled, Cypresses at the Union Buildings by Sydney Carter (1874-1945). The work shows the side profile of the Union Buildings, the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> seat of Government in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>. Short Biography: Sidney Carter was born in Enfield in Middlesex in the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07ssc">United Kingdom</a> in 1874. He studied at the Royal College of Art in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m04jpl">London</a> from 1895 to 1899. Carter came to South Africa in 1925 . He taught at the Witwatersrand College of Art. He passed away in Harrismith in the Free State in 1945.',
