    'An undated painting titled, Ironing Lady by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Joe Maseko (1940-2008).  Like in many of his works, Maseko painted about everyday life and little is known of the artist and his artworks. Short Biography: Joseph Ramapulane Maseko was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0729t">Soweto</a> in Johannesburg in 1940. He was a self-taught artist who began his art career in 1959. He was the designer of the throne of the Zulu King Goodwill Zwelithini kaBhekuzulu (1948-2021). Maseko exhibited his works from as early as the 1960s and had a solo exhibition in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m02cl1">Denver</a> Colorado in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09c7w0">the United States</a> in 1973. Maseko passed away in 2008.',
