    'Nils Andersen',
    '1962',
    'A <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m018ktp">Watercolor painting</a> by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m05b4w">Norwegian</a> / <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Nils Severin Andersen (1897-1972) titled <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m094jc">Fishing</a> <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m019jd">Boats</a>. Anderson spent the first 14 years of his life on his fatherï¿½s ship and therefore loved the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06npx">sea</a>. After he came to Durban he painted the coast and like in this painting depicted the day to day life of the people who lived from the sea. Short Biography: Nils Andersen was born in 1897 in Drammen Norway and immigrated to South Africa in 1911. He studied from 1924 to 1928 at the Natal Technical College. In 1940 he became an official war artist to the Natal Command of the Royal Navy. He passed away in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01tjvv">Durban</a> in 1972.',
