    'An etching by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Eric Mbatha (b.1948) titled, Meeting with Friends. Short Biography: Eric Mbatha, was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0729t">Soweto</a> in 1948. He received his training in 1971 at the Evangelical Lutheran Art and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01mrgs">Craft</a> Centre at Rorke''s Drift. Mbatha''s works have been featured in numerous exhibitions, including "Black South Africa: Contemporary Graphics" at the Brooklyn Museum in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m02_286">New York</a> in 1976, and he has been a visiting artist at Augsburg College in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0fpzwf">Minneapolis</a>, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09c7w0">USA</a>.',
