    'Staffordshire',
    '1815',
    'An English Staffordshire, pearl-ware plate depicts a central transfer print of the portrait of Z.K.H. de Prins <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01qwg0">van Oranje</a> (1792-1849). The plate commemorates the Dutch <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m011wzc">Prince, Willem II</a> after the Battle of Waterloo (18 June 1815) in the Napoleonic wars where he served as the commander of the 1 Allied corps at the young age of 23. This commemorative plate created by Staffordshire Pearlware is similar to cream-ware, but the glaze differs because of the addition of cobalt, which gives the glaze a blue tint. The shell-edged pearlware was a popular design that included a textured rim and either blue, green, red, or yellow glaze. The plate was donated by Louise van Gybland Oosterhoff  as a Dutch collection as well as documents on <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">Dutch</a> history to the University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> in 1946.',
