    'Eugene Zimmermann',
    '1914',
    'Satirical <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m04_tb">Map</a> of Europe created by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06mzp">Swiss</a> <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09c7w0">American</a> cartoonist <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m02mf7">Eugene</a> Zimmermann (1862-1935) and printed by W Nï¿½lting in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03hrz">Hamburg</a>, 1914. The map looks at Europe at the start of the First <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0cm2xh">World War (1914-1918</a>) it shows different people representing different countries during the war. <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06bnz">Russia</a> is represented by <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m03c40">Rasputin</a> trying to keep the hunger of the people away, Germany fights on two fronts, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0154j">Belgium</a> is drowning under the arm of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0345h">Germany</a>,  <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0f8l9c">France</a> is asking help from <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07ssc">Britain</a>, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06swt">Serbia and Montenegro</a> is crushed and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01znc_">Turkey</a> is blowing the winds of war.',
