    'A <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m06msq">sculpture</a> titled, Untitled Structure by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Ian Redelinghuys. Short biography: Ian Redelinghuys was born in 1949. He obtained both his Fine Art and Teachers Diploma at the Technikon Pretoria and MA (Art and Design) at the University of Wolverhampton in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07ssc">the UK</a>. He lectured in the Department of Applied of Fine and Applied Arts at the Tshwane University of Technology, where he was also Head of Department between 1992 and 2008. He taught part-time at the University of Pretoria for a number of years. Redelinghuys has exhibited extensively, both locally and abroad, including the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> Art Museum, Johannesburg Art Gallery, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01tjvv">Durban</a> Art Museum, Iziko South African National Gallery, Washington, New York and many more. His works are represented in a number of private and institutional collections both national and international.',
