    'An <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m011lx">acrylic</a> on canvas painting titled, Tissue I by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Magdel van Rooyen (b.1983). The work plays with the Afrikaans word, "Frommel" which means to crumple and "form" or shape. Van Rooyen  juxtaposes the ideas of shape and shapeless against each other. Short Biography: Magdel van Rooyen (Fourie) was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a> in 1983. She completed High School in 2001 at Sacred Heart College in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a>. She obtained her BA (Fine Arts) degree from the University of Pretoria in 2006 and her MA (Fine Arts) in 2012. Since 2007, van Rooyen is a part-time lecturer in the Department of Fine Arts at the University of Pretoria.',
