    'This lithograph titled Le Bateau Ivre (The Drunken boat) was created by the Dutch artist Adriana Johanna Wilhelmina (Jeanne) Bieruma-Oosting (1898-1994). The work was donated by Mr. Johannes Jacobus (Joop) Klant (1915-1994) after the Macfadyen Memorial Hall exhibition of August 1946, titled "Living Netherlands Graphic Artists". Le Bateau Ivre is a poem written in 1871 by the poet <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0149h0">Arthur Rimbaud (1854-1891</a>) and describes a lost <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m019jd">boat</a> sinking at sea. Short Biography: Adriana Johanna Wilhelmina (Jeanne) Bieruma-Oosting was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0cfss">Leeuwarden</a> in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">The Netherlands</a> in 1898. She studied at the school for Art and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01mrgs">Craft</a> in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0h095">Haarlem</a> and the Academy for Fine Art in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07g0_">The Hague</a>. In 1937 she won a bronze <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m020yd1">medal</a> at the world fair in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m05qtj">Paris</a> and she was awarded the Knights Order of Orange Nassau. She passed away in 1994 in Almen, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0vk6f">Lochem</a>.',
