    'Monica von Moltke',
    '1990',
    'A painting titled Moonbird by the German/ <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> Artist Monika von Moltke (1934-d.) The painting which shows a fossilised bird over an ancient landscape has a secondary title "<a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m02yrp">Fossilized</a> Bird". This is the second painting of the same subject, the first one was stolen in 1988 and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m028nyg">Von Moltke</a> tried to recapture the image that plagued her dreams. Short Biography: Monika Nona Paula von Mellenthin was born in 1934 in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0845b">Breslau</a>, Germany. She moved to South Africa in 1950 and studied at the Witwatersrand Technical College from 1951-1953. In the middle of the 70s she moved to West <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0345h">Germany</a> only to find herself back in South Africa as a teacher at FUBA, the Federated Union of Black Artists by 1982. Von Moltke passed away in the late 2000s in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a>, South Africa',
