    'A painting by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0h7x">Austrian</a>-<a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist Jean Welz (1900-1975) titled Karolus'' Farm. The painting was painted of an area that are covered by the Brandvlei Dam that was constructed in 1983. Short Biography: Jean Max Friedrich Welz (1900-1975) was born in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0b1mf">Salzburg</a> in Austria in 1900. He moved first to <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/g121p5z1h">Denmark</a> and then to <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0f8l9c">France</a> before finally moving to South Africa in 1937. As a qualified architect he worked in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0g284">Johannesburg</a> but contracted Tuberculosis and move to the Karoo  in the Western Cape. In 1943 he became Principal of the Hugo Naude Art School. He lived in Worcester South Africa until 1969 thereafter he moved to Rondebosch in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01yj2">Cape Town</a>. He passed away in 1975.',
