    'This contemporary work titled, Rhino dated 1995 by the San artist, Freciano Ndala (b. 1947). The work shows a typical landscape with a rhino, antelope,a guinea fowl and the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m07j7r">tree</a> of life. Ndala was part of the Platfontein Art Group, a relocated community of !Xu and Khwe people displaced from <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0j4b">Angola</a> during the wars of the 1970s and 1980s. They were resettled at Platfontein near Schmidtsdrift outside <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01tjpx">Kimberley</a> in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South Africa</a> and in the 1990s the community were resettled again at <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m05zxw4q">Wildebeest Kuil</a>.The community consists of two San tribes, the !Xun and the Khwe. ï¿½The San of Platfonteinï¿½ is a collective name used for both the !Xun and Khwe.',
