    'A lithograph titled Fï¿½nf Mï¿½dchen am Waldteich or Five girls at the forest pond by the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0345h">German</a> artist Otto Mueller (1874-1930). This work was done in an edition of 20 and obtained from an exhibition in 1935 at the University''s MacFadyen Memorial Hall. Short Biography: Otto Mueller was born in Liebau, Silesia. He study lithography in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m01bdwr">Gorlitz</a> and <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0845b">Breslau</a>. He moved to <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0156q">Berlin</a> in 1908 and became part of ''Die Bruke'', a <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09b9m">Dresden</a> based art group. In 1919 he became a professor at the Academy of Arts in Breslau, a place he taught until he passed away in 1930.',
