    'A <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m059j2">Dutch</a> Christmas plate made by <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m04825h">De Porceleyne Fles</a> in <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m029t1">Delft</a> in 1918. Many factories in Europe produced commemorative Christmas plates. This De Porceleyne Fles blue and white "Kerstmis" or Christmas 1918 plate, signifies the hope of bringing about final peace after <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0cm2xh">World War I</a>. The Delft plate was painted by JD van Velzen (1886-1938) a well-known artist at De Porceleyne Fles or Porcelain Jar factory.',
