    'An oil painting titled, Rugged Landscape is by the South African artist Margaret Slabbert (b.1956). The work was done as a commission for the former Principal of the University of Pretoria, Prof Calie Pistorius. Short Biography: Margaret Slabbert was born in 1956 in Pretoria using her maiden surname, Margaret Gradwell as a <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artist. She studied at University of Pretoria where she also became a lecturer in 1980 and in 1999 she became an associate Professor. Gradwellï¿½s work appears in private, corporate, public and diplomatic collections. Amongst others at the Mayorï¿½s Office of the City of Tshwane, University of <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">Pretoria</a>, Pretoria Art Museum, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0c59j">Pietersburg</a> Art Gallery, HSRC, Lifegro, Saambou, Klerksdorp Municipality, Department of Education and Training, Pretoria, Technikon, Pretoria, UNISA School for Business Leadership, SASOL, Telkom, ABSA Towers (commissioned work), and National Museum for Women in the Arts, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0rh6k">Washington DC</a>, <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m09c7w0">USA</a>.',
