    'Hans Nel',
    '1938',
    'A portrait of Professor Marthinus Lourens du Toit painted by the South African artist Hans Nel in 1938. Prof ML du Toit (1897-1938) established the Department of Afrikaans Art and Culture at the University of Pretoria in 1930. From 1931 until his death in 1938, du Toit initiated and arranged numerous art exhibitions at the University of Pretoria''s MacFadyen Hall, initiating an art scene for Pretoria and he was known as a stern patron of the arts for South <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0dg3n1">Africa</a>. This initiative in Pretoria brought <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0hzlz">South African</a> artists and international artists to the capital of the then, South African Union. The 1930s was considered a golden age in the development of art and art-related studies in the <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m067z4">city of Pretoria</a>, largely influenced by the University of Pretoria''s first art collection. Du Toit is recognised as the founder of the University of Pretoria''s art collection. There is very little literature about the South African artist, Hans Nel and the commission of this portrait.',
