    '1030/1220',
    'Archaeological human <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0975t">clay</a> figurine fragment excavated in 1998 South <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0dg3n1">African</a> Iron Age <a href="https://artsandculture.google.com/entity/m0h61">archaeological</a> site of K2, block 1, section 12, dating approximately AD 1030 - AD 1220. The figurine depicts a female torso from hips to middle. The cylindrical waist expands into well-rounded hips. The figurine is characterised by a protruding navel with ornate decoration surrounding it. The incised, double-linear decoration at the belly follows the shape of the navel; the decoration above the navel is linear and reflects the motif below the navel. On the back extending from the buttocks are two punctuated lines; one drawn vertically and the other curving to the right. To the left of the punctuated line is an incised motif in a branch-like formation. A perforation is evident below the decoration at the navel.',
